.SH NAME
ToggleEvent \- ToggleEvent
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]ToggleEvent\f[B]\f[R] interface represents an event
notifying the user an Element\(cqs state has changed.
.PP
This is the event object for the \f[CR]HTMLElement\f[R]
\f[CR]beforetoggle\f[R] and \f[CR]toggle\f[R] events, which fire on some
elements just before and just after they transition between showing and
hidden, respectively.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]beforetoggle\f[R] fires on popovers and \f[CR]<dialog>\f[R]
elements
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]toggle\f[R] fires on popovers, \f[CR]<dialog>\f[R] elements, and
\f[CR]<details>\f[R] elements
